### Terminologies in AGILE

Team \-\> Scrum Master (Dev lead, QA lead), Scrum( Developers & QA), Product Owner

Product owner: finalizes the requirements;  could be a BA or a project manager

* User Storys: features in a requirement  
* Epic: is the collection of all the user stories of a particular requirement  
* Product backlog: includes all the requirements

Scrum Master: consists of dev lead and QA lead

* Along with product owner Sets a timeline, selects priority user stories for epics, and prepares a “sprint backlog” with shortlisted user stories  
* Sprint: the timeline that is set

Scrum: consists of developers and QA

* Works with the sprint backlog  
* Works on bugs from previous sprint, current sprint backlog and defines next sprint backlogs
